.TH "pldm_check_fw_space" 9 "pldm_check_fw_space" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pldm_check_fw_space \- Verify that the firmware image has space left
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pldm_check_fw_space
.BI "(struct pldmfw_priv *data "  ","
.BI "size_t offset "  ","
.BI "size_t length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
pointer to private data
.IP "offset" 12
offset to start from
.IP "length" 12
length to check for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Verify that the firmware data can hold a chunk of bytes with the specified
offset and length.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success, or -EFAULT if the image does not have enough
space left to fit the expected length.
